article.headline: Quinnipiac 92, Lehigh 88
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Casey Cosgrove scored 10 of his 16 points after regulation to lead Quinnipiac to a 92-88 win over Lehigh in two overtimes Wednesday. Ed Zajac scored 17 points to lead six players in double figures for Quinnipiac (2-3). Cosgrove and Evann Baker each added 16. Marquis Hall led Lehigh (3-4) with 27 points and Zahir Carrington added 23. Cosgrove scored eight points in the first overtime, including a 3-pointer to start the period and another that gave Quinnipiac a four-point lead. But Lehigh's Matt Szalachowski and Bryan White hit back-to-back 3-pointers to tie it and force a second overtime. In the second extra session, DeMario Anderson scored five of Quinnipiac's 12 points and the Bobcats hit their final six free throws to seal the win. Quinnipiac held a 32-29 lead at the half of a game that featured 19 lead changes. A 3-pointer by Hall late in the second half helped give Lehigh a five-point lead. But the Bobcats scored six unanswered points to get within three with less than a minute to go and Bryan Geffen hit a 3-pointer with eight seconds left to force overtime.
